# migrated from tests/cases/coref_resolve.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test coref_resolve]
# gen216 (docs/plans/the-linguistic-glue.md, G2 — first pull from glue-bench's gap map):
# linguistic glue as a DETERMINISTIC operation, not an emergent field. A reference carries
# across turns: "rex is a dog" sets the recent entity, then the pronoun "it" in the next
# turn resolves to it and the resolved query is re-dispatched ("is rex a dog" -> Yes).
# Conservative: coref_resolve runs only as a FALLBACK (when the turn as-is wasn't
# understood) and claims only if a module answers the resolved turn, so it never hijacks a
# turn that already works. (The Italian counterpart is pro-drop — no "it" token to resolve
# — a distinct, harder pull recorded as a gap in glue-bench, not faked here.)
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> is it a dog
< Yes.

